# Code Review Guidelines

**Activation Mode:** Model Decision
**Description:** Apply when reviewing code, identifying issues, and providing feedback

## Review Criteria
- Check for adherence to coding standards and style guidelines
- Verify TypeScript types are properly defined and used
- Ensure proper error handling and edge case coverage
- Review for potential security vulnerabilities
- Check platform-specific implementations (iOS vs Android)

## Performance Considerations
- Look for unnecessary re-renders in React Native components
- Check for proper memoization and optimization
- Verify efficient data structures and algorithms
- Ensure proper resource cleanup and memory management
- Review list performance (FlatList vs ScrollView usage)
- Check image optimization and loading strategies

## Mobile-Specific Review Points
- Verify proper navigation implementation
- Check platform-specific code and styling
- Review accessibility implementation
- Ensure proper keyboard handling and safe area management
- Check for proper permission handling
- Review battery and performance impact

## Code Quality
- Assess code readability and maintainability
- Check for proper abstraction and separation of concerns
- Verify consistent naming conventions throughout
- Ensure adequate test coverage for new functionality
- Review React Native best practices adherence

## Architecture Review
- Validate component structure and hierarchy
- Check for proper separation of business logic
- Ensure consistent patterns across the codebase
- Review API design and data flow
- Validate navigation structure and deep linking

## Feedback Guidelines
- Provide constructive and specific feedback
- Suggest improvements with reasoning
- Highlight both positive aspects and areas for improvement
- Focus on the code, not the person writing it
- Include mobile-specific considerations in feedback